Service docker start or docker -d (to start daemon)

Docker info (system wide information)

Docker run -p 80:80 image_id (to start container with an image specifying ports) 

Docker run -p 80:80 -d --rm image_id --name myapp (detached and removed when stopped, with custom name)

Docker start/stop container_id(hex or name) (to start or stop a specific container)

Docker rm container name (list -- remove stopped containers)

Docker container prune (remove all stopped containers)

Docker images (list of images)

Docker rmi image_id(remove images, if not used by any container)

Docker image prune (remove unused images)

Docker build -t goals:latest  . (build with name:tag combination for image) 

Docker run -p 80:80 -d --rm goals:latest --name myapp (detached and removed when stopped, with custom name, with custom name:tag for image)

docker tag node:app jonrynn/node-app (rename image)

Docker login (for docker hub) docker logout (can still pull)

Docker image prune -a (delete all nonused images)

Docker pull jonrynn/node-app
